ir quickstart for AI agents

Goal:
  Produce portable, self-describing R scripts and Quarto documents.
  Put runtime metadata in frontmatter; keep the body plain R or Quarto code.

Mental model:
  `ir` reads frontmatter, resolves dependencies, materializes an ephemeral
  cached environment, then launches Rscript or Quarto with that environment.
  Do not call install.packages(), renv::restore(), groundhog, checkpoint, or
  custom CRAN snapshot setup from the artifact. Declare metadata; `ir` handles
  package installation and reuse.

R script frontmatter:
  #| packages:
  #|   - dplyr
  #|   - ggplot2
  #| r-version: ">= 4.3"
  #| isolated: true
  #| exclude-newer: "2025-01-15"

Quarto frontmatter:
  ---
  title: Report
  ir:
    packages:
      - dplyr
      - ggplot2
    r-version: ">= 4.3"
    isolated: true
    exclude-newer: "2025-01-15"
  ---

Python:
  Add `python-packages` and optional `python-version` to frontmatter.
  In Quarto, put those keys under `ir:` with the R runtime metadata.
  `ir` resolves a Python environment with reticulate's uv helper before launch,
  activates it for subprocesses, and sets RETICULATE_PYTHON. `ir render` also
  sets QUARTO_PYTHON and injects jupyter.
  Add `reticulate` under `packages` only when R code loads reticulate.
  `exclude-newer` also applies to Python unless `python-exclude-newer` is set.

Isolation:
  By default, the resolved R library is first on `.libPaths()` and ambient user
  libraries remain available. With `isolated: true` or `--isolated`, ambient
  user libraries are not available. Base, site, and system libraries remain.
  `rx` and `ir tool run` are isolated package-executable runs.

Package tools:
  Some R packages ship executables in exec/, bin/, or bin/<arch>/. Use `rx`
  or `ir tool run` to run those tools without installing the package, creating
  a project library, or installing them first.
  Tool runs resolve the provider package plus any `--with` dependencies into an
  isolated cached R library, then launch the selected executable. Ambient user
  R libraries are not used.
  Use tools for ad hoc package frontends. Use `ir tool install` for repeated
  shell use; installed tool libraries live outside the cache and survive
  `ir cache clean`. For durable analytical artifacts, prefer `ir run` or
  `ir render` with frontmatter.

Workflow:
  Use `--with PKG` while exploring; promote stable dependencies to frontmatter.
  Use `exclude-newer` for reproducible CRAN state.
  Write ordinary R after the metadata. Do not embed package-manager ceremony.

System requirements:
  R/Rscript must be available, either on PATH or selected with `rscript`.
  Use rig for `r-version` selection and date-only `exclude-newer` R selection.
  Quarto must be available for `ir render`. OS libraries and compilers required
  by packages remain system dependencies.

Commands:
  ir run script.R
  ir render report.qmd
  ir run --with cli -e 'cli::cli_alert_success("ok")'
  ir tool run btw --help
  rx btw --help
  rx --from btw btw --help

Argument boundaries:
  ir run --with cli script.R --input data.csv
      # `--with cli` is for ir; `--input data.csv` is passed to script.R.

  ir render --with ggplot2 report.qmd --to html
      # `--with ggplot2` is for ir; `--to html` is passed to Quarto.

  rx --from btw --with cli btw --help
      # `--from` and `--with` are for rx; `--help` is passed to the btw executable.

Inspection commands:
  ir --help
  ir run --help
  ir render --help
  ir tool run --help
  ir tool install --help
  rx --help
